\par\pard\plain \tx0\li360\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf6 This is the second scene in the book. The first scene consists of only one paragraph setting the stage for the book. In that scene, Evan is staring at the divorce document, focusing on the word \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93DIVORCE" as if it's the only word on the page. He wondered how a relationship with a storybook beginning ended so harshly.}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf6 Evan didn't see the divorce coming. He thought things were fine. He came home from a trip one day, excited to see Sarah. However, Sarah had packed up all her belongings, leaving only a note stating \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93This isn\u8217\'92t working anymore. I need some space." The next day he was served with divorce papers instructing him not to contact her directly. All communication is to pass through her attorneys.<!$Scr_Ps::3>}
